<subSubSection id="CFEAB4D43A0CFFA099FCC702ACCAF906" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="874FE75F3A0CFFA099FCC702ACCAF906" blockId="0.[151,1436,1180,2009]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA099FCC702A874FA84" bold="true" box="[199,316,1284,1307]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species for the first inattentive look could be taken for an 
<taxonomicName id="40F09CDC3A0CFFA09D3EC702AC7BFA84" authority="Hampson, 1906" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1906" box="[1029,1331,1284,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Athaumasta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA09D3EC702ADCCFA83" box="[1029,1156,1284,1308]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Athaumasta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E3619AAE3A0CFFA09DB0C702AC7BFA84" author="Hampson" box="[1163,1331,1284,1307]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1906) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum. British Museum Trustees, London, Taylor and Francis, 6, 1 - 532." type="journal article" year="1906">
Hampson, 
<number id="3138F5783A0CFFA09DC5C702AC7BFA84" box="[1278,1331,1284,1307]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="1906.0">1906</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, however the slenderer thorax, narrower, more elongated forewing with oblique termen and the patternless hindwing indicate its position within the genus 
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA09886C74FAB62FAFE" box="[445,554,1353,1377]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Bryoleuca</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName id="40F09CDC3A0CFFA09B05C74FABF5FAFE" box="[574,701,1353,1377]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Athaumasta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA09B05C74FABF5FAFE" box="[574,701,1353,1377]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Athaumasta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has robust thorax, broader forewing, and conspicuous pattern on hindwing). It belongs, according to its genitalia structure, to the 
<taxonomicName id="40F09CDC3A0CFFA09A7FC76AAAF8FA1B" box="[836,944,1388,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryoleuca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="raptricula">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA09A7FC76AAAF8FA1B" box="[836,944,1388,1412]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">raptricula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group which is characterized by large size of the female genitalia, very short ductus bursae, presence of elongated sclerotized longitudinal plate in anterior part of ductus bursae, sclerotized appendix bursae. The new species is especially close to 
<taxonomicName id="40F09CDC3A0CFFA09D0CC7B4ADA1FA56" box="[1079,1257,1457,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryoleuca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orthogramma">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA09D0CC7B4ADA1FA56" box="[1079,1257,1457,1481]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">B. orthogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1FCBFBDA3A0CFFA09DC2C7B4AC73FA56" box="[1273,1339,1458,1481]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1948,1970]" captionTargetBox="[259,1313,197,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[238,1336,191,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Bryoleuca spp., female genitalia. 7, B. pljushtchi, holotype, slide OP 2688 f; 8, B. orthogramma, slide OP 1099 f; 9, B. nahnybidai, slide OP 1043 f; 10, B. raptricula, slide OP 0577 f; 11, B. felina, slide OP 0576 f; 12, B. volodia, slide LR 6437 f." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238223/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
Fig. 
<number id="3138F5783A0CFFA09C16C7B4AC73FA56" box="[1325,1339,1458,1481]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
), though being externally strikingly different from all other congeners. The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="40F09CDC3A0CFFA09D1FC7D3ADE2FA73" box="[1060,1194,1492,1516]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryoleuca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pljushtchi">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA09D1FC7D3ADE2FA73" box="[1060,1194,1492,1516]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">B. pljushtchi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1FCBFBDA3A0CFFA09D82C7D2ADB0FA74" box="[1209,1272,1492,1515]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1948,1970]" captionTargetBox="[259,1313,197,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[238,1336,191,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Bryoleuca spp., female genitalia. 7, B. pljushtchi, holotype, slide OP 2688 f; 8, B. orthogramma, slide OP 1099 f; 9, B. nahnybidai, slide OP 1043 f; 10, B. raptricula, slide OP 0577 f; 11, B. felina, slide OP 0576 f; 12, B. volodia, slide LR 6437 f." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238223/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
Fig. 
<number id="3138F5783A0CFFA09DD1C7D2ADB0FA74" box="[1258,1272,1492,1515]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) differ from all relatives by the significantly larger size, large, practically rectangular antrum, smoothly sclerotized longitudinal plate in anterior part of ductus bursae, large appendix bursae with heavily sclerotized, cup-like apical plate. Comparing with 
<taxonomicName id="40F09CDC3A0CFFA09CBEC41CA848F9CB" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryoleuca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pljushtchi">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA09CBEC41CA848F9CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">B. pljushtchi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, only 
<taxonomicName id="40F09CDC3A0CFFA09878C43BA8F8F9CB" box="[323,432,1596,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryoleuca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="volodia">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA09878C43BA8F8F9CB" box="[323,432,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">B. volodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1FCBFBDA3A0CFFA09885C43BAB43F9CB" box="[446,523,1597,1620]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1948,1970]" captionTargetBox="[259,1313,197,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[238,1336,191,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Bryoleuca spp., female genitalia. 7, B. pljushtchi, holotype, slide OP 2688 f; 8, B. orthogramma, slide OP 1099 f; 9, B. nahnybidai, slide OP 1043 f; 10, B. raptricula, slide OP 0577 f; 11, B. felina, slide OP 0576 f; 12, B. volodia, slide LR 6437 f." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238223/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
Fig. 
<number id="3138F5783A0CFFA098CBC43BAB43F9CB" box="[496,523,1597,1620]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
) has relatively similar rectangular shape of antrum, but the other parts of the genitalia are, however, conspicuously different. The other related species, 
<taxonomicName id="40F09CDC3A0CFFA09AB9C466AD5AF9E9" box="[898,1042,1630,1655]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryoleuca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="raptricula">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA09AB9C466AD5AF9E9" box="[898,1042,1630,1655]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">B. raptricula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, (
<figureCitation id="1FCBFBDA3A0CFFA09D14C459ADCAF9E9" box="[1071,1154,1631,1654]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1948,1970]" captionTargetBox="[259,1313,197,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[238,1336,191,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Bryoleuca spp., female genitalia. 7, B. pljushtchi, holotype, slide OP 2688 f; 8, B. orthogramma, slide OP 1099 f; 9, B. nahnybidai, slide OP 1043 f; 10, B. raptricula, slide OP 0577 f; 11, B. felina, slide OP 0576 f; 12, B. volodia, slide LR 6437 f." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238223/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
Fig. 
<number id="3138F5783A0CFFA09D5CC459ADCAF9E9" box="[1127,1154,1631,1654]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="40F09CDC3A0CFFA09DA4C466AC49F9E9" box="[1183,1281,1630,1655]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryoleuca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felina">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA09DA4C466AC49F9E9" box="[1183,1281,1630,1655]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">B. felina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1FCBFBDA3A0CFFA09C2DC459AC21F9E9" box="[1302,1385,1631,1654]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1948,1970]" captionTargetBox="[259,1313,197,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[238,1336,191,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Bryoleuca spp., female genitalia. 7, B. pljushtchi, holotype, slide OP 2688 f; 8, B. orthogramma, slide OP 1099 f; 9, B. nahnybidai, slide OP 1043 f; 10, B. raptricula, slide OP 0577 f; 11, B. felina, slide OP 0576 f; 12, B. volodia, slide LR 6437 f." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238223/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
Fig. 
<number id="3138F5783A0CFFA09C75C459AC21F9E9" box="[1358,1385,1631,1654]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
), 
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA09CBEC466A854F906" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">B. orthogramm</emphasis>
a, and 
<taxonomicName id="40F09CDC3A0CFFA09859C484A8B0F906" box="[354,504,1665,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryoleuca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nahnybidai">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA09859C484A8B0F906" box="[354,504,1665,1689]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">B. nahnybidai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1FCBFBDA3A0CFFA09B3CC484AB0EF906" box="[519,582,1666,1689]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1948,1970]" captionTargetBox="[259,1313,197,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[238,1336,191,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Bryoleuca spp., female genitalia. 7, B. pljushtchi, holotype, slide OP 2688 f; 8, B. orthogramma, slide OP 1099 f; 9, B. nahnybidai, slide OP 1043 f; 10, B. raptricula, slide OP 0577 f; 11, B. felina, slide OP 0576 f; 12, B. volodia, slide LR 6437 f." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238223/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
Fig. 
<number id="3138F5783A0CFFA09B03C484AB0EF906" box="[568,582,1666,1689]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) have narrow, shield-like antrum and wrinkled anterior part of corpus bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CFEAB4D43A0CFFA199FCC4A3A8BFFF4E" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="597" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" type="description">
<paragraph id="874FE75F3A0CFFA199FCC4A3A8BFFF4E" blockId="0.[151,1436,1180,2009]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1436,152,313]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="597" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA099FCC4A3A8E1F923" bold="true" box="[199,425,1701,1724]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Description. Adults</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1FCBFBDA3A0CFFA09886C4A3AB49F923" box="[445,513,1701,1724]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1961,1983]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,374,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,367,1937]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Bryoleuca spp., adults, females. 1, B. pljushtchi, holotype, Afghanistan, Sabzil; 2, B. orthogramma, Mongolia; 3, B. raptricula, Hungary; 4, B. felina, Hungary; 5, B. volodia, Vietnam; 6, B. nahnybidai, Kazakhstan." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238222/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
Fig. 
<number id="3138F5783A0CFFA098CFC4A3AB49F923" box="[500,513,1701,1724]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity id="40084ABA3A0CFFA09BAFC4A3ABA0F923" box="[660,744,1701,1724]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" unit="mm" value="35.0">35 mm</quantity>
. Head, collar, thorax, tegulae and abdomen pale clay-yellow. Forewing elongated; apex rounded; outer margin with straight upper part (from apex to vein M 
<number id="3138F5783A0CFFA09DA9C4D1ADD1F97C" box="[1170,1177,1751,1763]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="3.0">3</number>
) and oblique lower part (from vein M 
<number id="3138F5783A0CFFA09812C4FAA878F897" box="[297,304,1788,1800]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="3.0">3</number>
to vein A 
<number id="3138F5783A0CFFA098A4C4FAA8EEF897" box="[415,422,1788,1800]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="1.0">1</number>
). Ground colour pale clay-yellow; elements of noctuid pattern dark brown; basal line as dark dot on vein A; subbasal and antemedial lines undulate; median fascia present, diffuse, passing through orbicular stigma; postmedial line dentate, sinuous; subterminal line distinct; pre-apical patch small; reniform stigma rather elliptical; orbicular stigma large, lunulate; claviform stigma absent; cilia as ground colour. Hindwing as ground colour but lighter in shade; discal lunule absent. 
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0CFFA098DDC57CABEBF80E" bold="true" box="[486,675,1914,1937]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1FCBFBDA3A0CFFA09B88C57CABBFF80E" box="[691,759,1914,1937]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1948,1970]" captionTargetBox="[259,1313,197,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[238,1336,191,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Bryoleuca spp., female genitalia. 7, B. pljushtchi, holotype, slide OP 2688 f; 8, B. orthogramma, slide OP 1099 f; 9, B. nahnybidai, slide OP 1043 f; 10, B. raptricula, slide OP 0577 f; 11, B. felina, slide OP 0576 f; 12, B. volodia, slide LR 6437 f." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238223/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
Fig. 
<number id="3138F5783A0CFFA09BDCC57CABBFF80E" box="[743,759,1914,1937]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor large, wide, densely covered with hair-like setae; anterior apophyses long, posterior apophyses slightly longer and thinner than anterior apophyses. Antrum broad, ventral plate large, rectangular; subgenital plate (
<number id="3138F5783A0CFFA09B58C5C4AB38F846" box="[611,624,1986,2009]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="8.0">8</number>
th abdominal segment) wide, well sclerotized; ductus bursae short; corpus bursae elliptical, membranous, posterior part with longitudinal sclerotized plate; appendix bursae large with heavily sclerotized, cup-like apical plate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CFEAB4D43A0DFFA199FCC2DBAACFFE88" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="874FE75F3A0DFFA199FCC2DBAACFFE88" blockId="1.[151,1436,152,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0DFFA199FCC2DBAB41FF6B" bold="true" box="[199,521,221,244]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Distribution and bionomics.</emphasis>
The new species is known from its 
<typeStatus id="584B59FD3A0DFFA19AA1C2DBAA80FF6B" box="[922,968,221,244]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">type</typeStatus>
locality, 
<collectingCountry id="FFE7A7CF3A0DFFA19D14C2DBADFCFF6B" box="[1071,1204,221,244]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, Sabzil. 
<taxonomicName id="40F09CDC3A0DFFA19C28C2DBACD4FF6B" box="[1299,1436,220,244]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryoleuca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pljushtchi">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0DFFA19C28C2DBACD4FF6B" box="[1299,1436,220,244]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">B. pljushtchi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits floodplain meadow bordering dry rocky hill biotope (
<figureCitation id="1FCBFBDA3A0DFFA19A10C306AA32FE88" box="[811,890,256,279]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="3.[151,244,1070,1092]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1047]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1047]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 13. Afghanistan, Sabzil, 2850 m, type locality of B. pljushtchi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238224/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">
Fig. 
<number id="3138F5783A0DFFA19A66C306AA32FE88" box="[861,890,256,279]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CFEAB4D43A0DFFA199FCC324AD86FEA6" box="[199,1230,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="874FE75F3A0DFFA199FCC324AD86FEA6" blockId="1.[151,1436,152,313]" box="[199,1230,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis id="B5843B4D3A0DFFA199FCC324A808FEA6" bold="true" box="[199,320,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name is dedicated to Igor Pljushtch, collector of the 
<typeStatus id="584B59FD3A0DFFA19AC5C324AD13FEA6" box="[1022,1115,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
